        Gets Basic Boundary by Address Gets Basic Boundary by Address
        Parameters:
        address - Address around which Basic Boundary is requested (required)
        distance - This is width of the buffer (in a complete circular buffer, it would be radius of the buffer). This has to be a positive number. (required)
        country - Three digit ISO country code (optional, default to USA)
        distanceUnit - Longitude around which Basic Boundary is requested (optional, default to feet)
        resolution - This is resolution of the buffer. Curves generated in buffer are approximated by line segments and it is measured in segments per circle. The higher the resolution, the smoother the curves of the buffer but more points would be required in the boundary geometry. Number greater than 0 and in multiple of 4. If not in 4, then it is approximated to nearest multiple of 4. (optional)
        responseSrs - The spatial reference system to express the response in. By default, it would be epsg:4326 (optional, default to epsg:4326)

        Gets travel Boundary by Distance Returns the travel boundary based on travel distance.

        costs - Travel distance(s) (required)

        country - Three digit ISO country code. (optional, default to USA)
        maxOffroadDistance - Maximum distance to allow travel off the road network. (optional)

        destinationSrs - Desired coordinate system of the travel boundary. (optional)
        majorRoads - Whether to include all roads in the calculation or just major roads. (optional, default to false)
        returnHoles - Whether to return holes, which are areas within the larger boundary that cannot be reached within the desired distance. (optional, default to false)
        returnIslands - Whether to return islands, which are small areas outside the main boundary that can be reached within the desired distance. (optional, default to false)
        simplificationFactor - Number between 0.0 and 1.0 where 0.0 is very simple and 1.0 means the most complex. (optional, default to 0.5)
        bandingStyle - Style of banding to be used in the result. (optional, default to Donut)
        historicTrafficTimeBucket - Whether routing calculation uses the historic traffic speeds. (optional, default to None)
        defaultAmbientSpeed - The speed to travel when going off a network road to find the travel boundary (for all road types). (optional)
        ambientSpeedUnit - The unit of measure to use to calculate the ambient speed. (optional, default to MPH)

        TravelBoundaries
